== Caramelised Apples ==

Finely chop the @red chilli{1/2}. Peel and very, very finely chop the @carrot{1}(peeled and diced into ½cm cubes if your skills allow!). Peel and core the @Cox's apple{1} before chopping into 1cm cubes. Peel and finely chop the @echalion shallot{1}(peeled and finely chopped). Cut the @sliced spring greens{1/2}(leaves only) into roughly 1cm slices, discard the tough root. Finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{1/2}(finely chopped).

Melt a knob of @?butter{1%knob} in a #non-stick frying pan{} on medium-low heat. > If you don't have any butter, use a splash of olive oil.

Toss in your apple, a sprinkle of @?sugar{} (if you have some) and a splash of water, place a lid on the pan. Allow to cook for ~{10-15%minutes} or until your apple has softened. > Remove the lid to thicken the caramelised apple in the last few mins.

When the ~{10%minutes} are up, take the pan off the heat and leave to the side with the lid on.

== Roasted Duck ==

Preheat your #oven{} to 180 degrees and season the @duck breasts{2} with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cut three slices across your duck skin with a sharp #knife{} and lay in a cold #griddle pan{} skin-side down (just use a #frying pan{} if you don't have a griddle pan). Cook on medium-low heat for about ~{7%minutes} or until the fat is crisp and golden.

Transfer to a #baking tray{} skin-side up and cook for ~{7%minutes} on the top shelf of your oven.

> We like our duck pink, if you like it well done, cook it for 15 mins in the oven, if you like it rare, cook it for 5 mins in the oven.

== Spiced Lentils ==

While your duck is cooking, you can get on with the lentils. Put a frying pan on medium heat with a drizzle of oil and add your chilli, carrot and shallot. Cook for ~{5%minutes} until soft.

Drain and thoroughly rinse your @green lentils{1} before adding to the pan, together with the @vegetable stock pot{1/2} and the @water{75%ml}.

Cook for ~{3%minutes}, then take the pan off the heat. Cover with a #lid{} and leave until it's time to serve.

== Greens ==

Once your duck is cooked, remove from your oven and leave it to rest for a few mins.

> Leaving meat to rest on a warm plate, allows the juices to redistribute throughout the meat, so that every mouthful is nice and juicy.

Pour out all but a drizzle of oil from the pan you fried your duck in and pop on medium-high heat. Once hot, add your spring greens along with a pinch of salt and a good grind of pepper. Fry for ~{3-4%minutes} until your spring greens have softened.

== To Serve ==

Stir your parsley through your spiced lentils. Serve your duck on top of your spiced lentils with a healthy dollop of your caramelised apples and your greens on the side.